    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. looking at the actual arguments though, it feels like there's a lot of talk about how \"innovation\" is used as a shield by these companies to avoid regulation. do you think the current regulatory push is actually a legitimate attempt to fix a broken market, or is it more just political theater/overreach?",
