      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Many observers see the regulatory push as a necessary response to how tech monopolies can slow down genuine competition and innovation through exclusionary tactics. Proponents argue that traditional antitrust law was not designed for modern digital markets, necessitating updated rules to ensure fair play. Conversely, critics suggest that heavy-handed regulation could stifle the very innovation these companies drive, acting as bureaucratic overreach. Ultimately, the debate centers on whether the current structure allows for \"competitive innovation\" or simply entrenches entrenched power.",
      "source": "target",
