      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When a significant body of legal scholars points to systemic flaws, it certainly shifts the burden of proof onto the incumbents to demonstrate their benefits are purely pro-competitive. This widespread critique suggests the \"innovation\" defense is increasingly viewed by experts not as a shield, but as a secondary argument against demonstrable market power. Whether it's \"fair\" depends on one's view of market mechanics, but the consensus strongly indicates the current framework is inadequate for today's digital economy.",
      "source": "target",
